VALUES
(41, 4, 32, 26, 31, 3, 10, 'great branches; so that the fowls', 'Growth and Shelter Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of great trees providing shelter and support for birds and beasts. The ''great branches'' in Mark parallel the ''branches'' and ''shadow'' of the Assyrian cedar in Ezekiel, highlighting the theme of growth and protection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 32, 19, 80, 9, 11, 'shadow of it', 'Growth and Shelter Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of a plant that provides shelter. Mark describes a plant that becomes greater than all herbs, while Psalms speaks of a plant whose boughs cover the hills, providing shadow.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 32, 19, 91, 1, 1, 'shadow of it', 'Shadow of Protection', 'This connection highlights the theme of shelter and safety. Both passages emphasize the idea of finding refuge under a protective shadow.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 32, 22, 2, 3, 3, 'shadow of it', 'Connection of Growth and Shelter', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of shelter and growth. In Mark, the great branches provide shade for birds, while in Song of Solomon, the beloved is compared to a tree offering shade and sweet fruit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 32, 23, 11, 9, 9, 'great branches; so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it', 'Growth and Protection Imagery', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth and safety. Mark 4:32 describes a tree providing shelter, while Isaiah 11:9 envisions a peaceful environment where harm is absent.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 33, 40, 13, 34, 35, 'with many such parables', 'Connection of Parables in Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the use of parables by Jesus in his teachings. Mark notes that he spoke ''with many such parables,'' while Matthew highlights that ''without a parable spake he not unto them.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 33, 43, 16, 12, 12, 'as they were able to hear it', 'Communication of Complex Truths', 'Both passages emphasize the limitation of understanding. Mark 4:33 notes that Jesus spoke in parables as they were able to hear it, while John 16:12 indicates that there are many things He wishes to convey, but they cannot bear them now.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 33, 46, 3, 1, 2, 'as they were able to hear it', 'Spiritual Maturity and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual maturity and the ability to comprehend deeper truths. Both passages emphasize the necessity of being able to bear the teachings given, with Mark referencing the audience''s capacity to hear and Paul addressing the Corinthians'' inability to receive more substantial teaching.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 33, 58, 5, 11, 14, 'as they were able to hear it', 'Hearing and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of hearing and understanding in both passages. Mark 4:33 mentions the ability to hear, while Hebrews 5:11 addresses being ''dull of hearing'' and needing to return to basic teachings.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 43, 16, 25, 25, 'spake he not unto them', 'Use of Parables and Proverbs', 'This connection highlights the use of parables and proverbs in teaching. Both passages emphasize a transition from speaking in parables or proverbs to a clearer revelation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 41, 4, 10, 10, 'when they were alone', 'Understanding Parables and Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus teaching through parables and the subsequent explanation to his disciples. The connection illustrates the distinction between public teaching and private clarification.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 42, 24, 27, 27, 'expounded all things to his disciples', 'Expounding the Scriptures', 'This connection highlights the act of expounding, where both Jesus explains deeper meanings to his followers. In Mark, he expounds to his disciples privately, while in Luke, he expounds on the scriptures concerning himself, showing a continuity in teaching.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 40, 13, 36, 43, 'he expounded all things to his disciples', 'Teaching Through Parables', 'This connection highlights how Jesus used parables to teach the crowds and then provided deeper explanations to his disciples. Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding the messages behind the parables, as seen in the disciples'' request for clarification in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 40, 15, 15, 20, 'he expounded all things to his disciples', 'Understanding of Parables', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding parables. In Mark, Jesus explains parables to his disciples, while in Matthew, Peter seeks clarification on a parable, indicating a need for deeper understanding.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 42, 8, 9, 10, 'he expounded all things to his disciples', 'Understanding Parables and Mysteries', 'Both passages emphasize the teaching method of Jesus using parables to convey deeper truths. Mark highlights that Jesus explained things privately to his disciples, while Luke notes that understanding these mysteries is given specifically to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 34, 41, 7, 17, 23, NULL, 'Understanding of Defilement', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding spiritual truths. In both passages, Jesus emphasizes the importance of inner purity over external actions, indicating that true defilement comes from within rather than from external sources.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 40, 8, 18, 18, 'unto the other side', 'Journey to the Other Side', 'Both passages emphasize the command to depart ''unto the other side,'' highlighting a shared narrative moment in Jesus'' ministry. This connection illustrates the movement of Jesus and his disciples across the water.', 'parallel', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 42, 8, 22, 22, NULL, 'Journey to the Other Side', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to ''go over unto the other side,'' highlighting a shared moment in Jesus'' ministry. This connection illustrates the continuity of events in the accounts of Mark and Luke.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 40, 14, 22, 22, 'Let us pass over unto the other side', 'Journey to the Other Side', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to cross to ''the other side,'' highlighting a shared moment of transition for Jesus and his disciples. This connection illustrates a common theme of movement and purpose in their ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 41, 8, 13, 13, 'Let us pass over unto the other side', 'Journey to the Other Side', 'Both passages emphasize the act of crossing to ''the other side,'' highlighting a recurring theme of movement and transition in Jesus'' ministry. This connection illustrates the significance of travel in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 43, 6, 25, 25, 'the other side', 'Journey Across the Sea', 'This connection highlights the movement across the sea, as indicated by ''the other side'' in both passages. The disciples'' journey in Mark leads to their encounter with Jesus in John, emphasizing the significance of this transition.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 41, 5, 21, 21, 'Let us pass over unto the other side', 'Journey Across the Sea', 'Both passages emphasize the act of crossing over to the other side, highlighting a significant transition in Jesus'' ministry. The movement from one side of the sea to the other serves as a narrative link between the events described.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 35, 43, 6, 1, 1, 'Let us pass over unto the other side', 'Journey Across the Sea', 'This connection highlights the movement of Jesus and his disciples across the Sea of Galilee. Both passages emphasize the act of crossing to the other side of the sea, indicating a continuation of Jesus'' ministry.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 36, 41, 3, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Ships in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of a ship in relation to Jesus'' ministry. In Mark 3:9, a small ship is mentioned to manage the crowd, while Mark 4:36 describes Jesus taking a ship with his disciples after dismissing the multitude.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 36, 41, 4, 1, 1, NULL, 'Teaching by the Sea Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the setting by the sea, highlighting the transition from teaching to action. The multitude''s presence in Mark 4:1 leads to the subsequent journey in Mark 4:36.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 36, 41, 5, 2, 2, 'even as he was in the ship', 'Journey from the Sea to the Tombs', 'This connection highlights the transition from the ship to the encounter with the man in the tombs. Both passages emphasize the movement of Jesus and his disciples, indicating a significant shift in location and context.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 36, 41, 5, 21, 21, NULL, 'Journey Across the Sea', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus traveling by ship, indicating a continuous journey across the sea. The mention of ''ship'' in both verses highlights the movement of Jesus and the gathering of people around him.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 37, 40, 8, 23, 24, 'great storm of wind', 'Storm at Sea Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a great storm that threatens the ship. The descriptions of the tempest and the ship being covered with waves create a parallel narrative of distress during the journey.', 'parallel', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 37, 18, 1, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Great Winds', 'Both passages emphasize the occurrence of a ''great wind'' that brings destruction. In Mark, the storm threatens the ship, while in Job, the wind causes the collapse of a house, leading to tragedy.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 37, 42, 8, 22, 23, 'storm of wind', 'Connection of Storm Narratives', 'Both passages emphasize a storm affecting a ship, highlighting the peril faced by the disciples. The description of the storm and the ship being filled with water is a common theme in both accounts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
